    {
      "id": "scenario_coal_s1",
      "name": "Cold Start — Bring the Plant Online",
      "description": "The coal plant has been shut down for scheduled maintenance and is ready to restart. Both control switches are open, the boiler is off, and the plant is disconnected from the grid. Close the drive motor switch to start the feedwater pump shaft train, then open the ECV control switch to admit feedwater. Close the drain valve V1 to seal the fluid circuit, activate the boiler, and wait for the steam turbines to reach operating speed. Before connecting to the grid, close the emergency bypass switch SWI3 to establish the backup power path. Grid export must be stable with V1 closed and SWI3 engaged to complete startup.",
      "difficulty": "tutorial",
