      "id": "scenario_coal_s2",
      "name": "Normal Shutdown — Planned Outage Procedure",
      "description": "The plant is running normally and a planned maintenance outage has been scheduled. Execute the correct shutdown sequence to bring the plant safely offline. Disconnect the generator from the grid first to prevent a hard trip, then deactivate the boiler and allow steam flow to collapse. Isolate the feedwater circuit by opening SWI1 to close ECV1, then stop the drive motor via SWI2. Finally, open the emergency bypass switch SWI3 to return the plant to its fully isolated pre-maintenance state.",
