    {
      "id": "scenario_coal_s3",
      "name": "Cooler Failure — Emergency Isolation",
      "description": "The cooling fan on COO1 has seized, causing the recirculating loop to carry uncondensed steam back to VAP1's inlet. VAP1 has auto-tripped on a steam_inlet fault, collapsing generation and disconnecting the generator from the grid. SWI1, SWI2, and SWI3 remain closed — the drive motor is still running and admitting feedwater into a dead circuit. Secure the plant before TOR1 sustains dry-run damage: open SWI1 to close ECV1 and isolate the feedwater inlet, stop the drive motor by opening SWI2, then open the emergency bypass SWI3 to fully de-energise the control bus.",
      "difficulty": "medium",
